[section [title Render Targets] [id di.render-target]]
[subsection [title Overview] [id di.render-target.overview]]
[paragraph]
A [term [type term] render target] is a rectangular region of memory allocated
on the GPU that can accept the results of a rendering operation.

[subsection [title Types] [id di.render-target.types]]
[paragraph]
In the [term [type package] r2] package, render targets are instances of
[link-ext [target "apidocs/com/io7m/r2/rendering/targets/R2RenderTargetType.html"] R2RenderTargetType].